{"title": "Instant People: Just Add Water!", "content": "Someone's body is reduced to powder, then reconstituted. Comes in two types: living-to-living and dead-to-living.\n\nLiving-to-living is usually Phlebotinum-based, and may be described as dehydrating the body or reducing it to its \"basic elements.\" It's technically a form of suspended animation. Dehydrated storage on a large scale (a.k.a. \"instant Mooks, just add water\") is a usually-comic sub-subtype.\n\nDead-to-living is usually magic-based, and often uses ashen remains.\n\nBecause powder is easily scattered and easily mixed, damage to the reduced body is an implicit possibility, and may result in Came Back Wrong. Sometimes (particularly when the method is given as \"dehydration\"), compact, friable solids are used instead, and the danger is that they will be crushed.\n\nSee also: Fossil Revival, No Body Left Behind, People Jars, Pulling Themselves Together, Taken for Granite.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/InstantPeopleJustAddWater", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/RanmaOneHalf", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Megamind", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/BatmanTheMovie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DraculaPrinceOfDarkness", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/HPLovecraft", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheCaseOfCharlesDexterWard", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Necroscope", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Discworld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekTheOriginalSeries", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Ultraviolet", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/MyFavoriteMartian", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/CallOfCthulhu", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/DungeonsAndDragons", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MonkeyIsland2LeChucksRevenge", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Webcomic/LookingForGroup", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DuckDodgersInTheTwentyFourthAndAHalfCentury", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/DaffyDuck", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/BugsBunny", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/CountDuckula", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Beetlejuice", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/Ben10UltimateAlien", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/LiloAndStitchTheSeries"], "non_media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Phlebotinum", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/HumanPopsicle", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Mook", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CameBackWrong", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/LiterallyShatteredLives", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/FossilRevival", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/NoBodyLeftBehind", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PeopleJars", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/PullingThemselvesTogether", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TakenForGranite", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/CameBackWrong", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ShoutOut", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Recap/StarTrekS2E22ByAnyOtherName", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VillainOfTheWeek", "http://www.startrek.com/legacy_media/images/200303/tos-050-two-enterprise-crew-me/320x240.jpg", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Redshirt", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/DisintegratorRay", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/MacGuffin", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/Mooks", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/BreakingTheFourthWall", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/VegetarianVampire", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/TooDumbToLive"]}